          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Polarization in the 16-O(n,n) reaction"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "2ITYPAD"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 5.5MeV Van de Graaff,at the Laboratori",
                " Nazionali di Lignaro, in pulsed operation",
                " using pulsed proton and deuteron beams by (1/2)",
                " micro-A in mean current and by less than 2ns in",
                " pulse duration."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "POLNS",
                  "P-LI7"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Lithium-7 was a solid target, 1 mg/cm2",
                " thick, obtained from evaporation of Li-F."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "POLNS",
                  "D-C12"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Carbon-12 was a solid target, 1 mg/cm2",
                " thick, obtained from deposition of colloidal graphite",
                " suspension."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "POLNS",
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Deuterium was a gaseous target,.4 mg/cm2",
                " thick. The neutrons of all three reactions were",
                " polarized."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Liquid oxigen cylinder(16 cm high,6 cm in diam),",
                " contained in a polyethylene bag(.15 mm thick),placed",
                " inside a cylindrical hole(6 cm diam) in a polystirol",
                " cylinder(48 cm high,41 cm diam,0.01 g/cm3 in density),",
                " whose vertical axis was 108 cm from the neutron source",
                ".Oxygen was considered to be practically 8-O-16."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " For details see NP/A 181."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " pulse height and time information."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fourteen NE213 liquid scintillators placed at",
                " 100 cm from the O-target,in a water filed",
                " cylindrical container (16 cm high,4.8 cm diam.),",
                " Seven on the left and seven on the right of the",
                " neutron collimated beam.",
                ".The left-right counter system,together with the",
                " O-target,could be rotated about a vertical axis",
                " going through the neutron source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".In order to obtain the polarization p(e,teta) from the",
                " initial exp-data,i.e.left-right ratios,authors used",
                " previous works and data on the polarization of",
                " neutrons issued from the 3 n-source reactions used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".A phase shift analysis on the polarization data with",
                " the cross section data at the same energies,has been",
                " carried out,with the aim of improving the agreement",
                " between the phase shift calculations and the",
                " experimental results.",
                ".A phase shift table resulting from least square fits",
                " of polarization and cross section data has been given."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "STATUS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "status": [
                  "TABLE"
                ],
                "subentry_number": null,
                "author": null,
                "reference": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " .Tbl. III, IV from NC/A 31."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The effect of dead time and of the detector efficiency",
                " were neglected in evaluating the experimental left-",
                " right ratios,but not the relative cross section",
                " measurements for which they were taken into account",
                " as well as the pulse bias changes and the second",
                " neutron group in the 7-Li(p,n) source and they gave",
                " rise to a sum of error ranging from 3 to 6%.",
                ".Experimental values of left-right ratios and of cross-",
                " sections were corrected for multiple scattering in the",
                " sample and for finite angular resolution by means of",
                " monte-carlo calculations.",
                ".Previous data were used in correcting the present",
                " experimental data.",
                ".Background subtracted."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The statistical uncertainty on left-right ratios are",
                " in the range of 0.01 to 0.04%,except for the 3 MeV",
                " neutrons produced by 12-C(d,n)reaction at 60 degrees.",
                ".Uncertainty on energy was 50 keV for Li-7(p,n)",
                " source,and 100 keV for the other sources."
              ]
            }
          ],
